Here is an example of how to generate a table of contents automatically in a LaTeX document:
```
\documentclass{article}

% Make sure to include the tocdepth package to control the depth of the TOC
\usepackage{tocdepth}

% Set the depth of the TOC to  , which means sections and subsections will be included
\settocdepth{subsection}

\begin{document}

% Generate the table of contents
\tableofcontents

\section{Introduction}
This is the introduction section.

\subsection{Background}
This is the background subsection.

\section{Methodology}
This is the methodology section.

\subsection{Data Collection}
This is the data collection subsection.

